articles.title: Curriculum Vitae
articles.contents:
Interests
Career goals center around utilizing spatial data to foster sustainable use of our marine systems
Currently living and working in Santa Barbara, California
Avid beach volleyball player and aspiring surfer
Education
Expected 2022 ~ Masters of Environmental Science and Management Bren School of Environmental Science & Management, University of California, Santa Barbara Specialization in Coastal Marine Resource Management and Conservation Planning
2018 ~ Bachelors of Science from University of California, Los Angeles

            Anastasia is currently in her first year at the Bren School of Environmental Science and Management at UCSB pursuing her Masters Degree. After receiving her bachelor’s degree in Biology from UCLA, Anastasia worked for NASA DEVELOP addressing issues in environmental science through GIS and remote sensing. Anastasia is looking to apply geospatial science to effectively manage marine ecosystems.
